Two votes of the Commons assembled in Parliament declaring the forces that are now come out of Scotland into England under the command of the Duke Hamilton, enemies to this kingdom; and all persons of the English or Irish nation that have invited, or voluntarily ayded or assisted them, are traytors and rebels. Die Veneris, 14 Julii, 1648. England and Wales. Parliament. House of Commons.
1 sheet ([1] p.)
Printed for Edward Husband, Printer to the Honourable House of Commons, London : July 24. 1648.
The second vote is dated: Die Jovis, 20 Julii, 1648. Signed: H: Elsynge, Cler. Parl. D. Com. Reproduction of the original in the British Library.
